PHASE 5: MAINTENANCE & RELAPSE PREVENTION
Monthly:

Fecal calprotectin monitoring (home tests now available — Calprolab, etc.) — catches mucosal re-inflammation before it becomes clinical
Symptom/food/stress journal review
Sleep quality audit

Every 3–6 months:

CRP, CBC, metabolic panel
Vitamin D recheck + dose adjust
Medication trough levels (if on biologic)

Every 12–18 months:

Colonoscopy with biopsies targeting histologic remission
Reassess step-down eligibility if in deep remission


RED FLAGS — What to Avoid or Watch For
Avoid:

❌ NSAIDs — triggers flares reliably
❌ Antibiotic courses without probiotic restoration protocol — devastating to already-depleted microbiome
❌ High-dose probiotic marketing without strain-specific evidence — most probiotic products have no UC RCT data
❌ Long-term corticosteroid use — bone density loss, adrenal suppression, immunosuppression without mucosal healing
❌ Unmonitored biologic therapy without TDM — flying blind
❌ Ignoring mental health — proven relapse accelerant
❌ Online protocols without colonoscopic confirmation — symptoms are unreliable proxies for mucosal status

Red flag symptoms requiring urgent GI contact:

⚠️ >6 bloody stools/day + fever — acute severe UC, needs hospitalization
⚠️ Abdominal rigidity or rebound tenderness — toxic megacolon risk
⚠️ Sudden pain resolution in longstanding severe colitis — perforation risk
⚠️ New joint pain, eye redness, or skin lesions — extraintestinal manifestations signaling systemic disease activity


